Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE A, PART IV, SECTION A, LINE 1:
Form990ScheduleAPartVIGrp.ExplanationTxt: SUPPORTED ORGANIZATIONS ARE CURRENT MEMBERS OF THE CONSORTIUM. SUPPORTED ORGANIZATIONS WERE DESIGNATED IN ACM'S ARTICLES OF ASSOCIATION AND ADDITIONAL SUPPORTED ORGANIZATIONS HAVE BEEN ADDED OVER TIME.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE USED TO FUND GRANTS BASED ON THE REQUIREMENTS OF EACH GRANT AS WELL AS A SOURCE OF INCOME FOR THE ORGANIZATION.

ACM IS AN ORGANIZATION DESCRIBED IN SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND THUS IS GENERALLY NOT SUBJECT TO TAX. IN ADDITION, THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE HAS DETERMINED THAT THE ACM IS NOT A PRIVATE FOUNDATION WITHIN THE MEANING OF SECTION 509(A) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA REQUIRE ACM TO EVALUATE TAX POSITIONS TAKEN BY ACM AND RECOGNIZE A TAX LIABILITY IF ACM HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES. ACM IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.

FACULTY DEVELOPMENT FUNDS AND STIPENDS ARE AWARDED IN A COMPETITIVE PROCESS WITH FACULTY PROPOSING VARIOUS PROJECTS AND COLLABORATIVE ACTIVITIES. RECIPIENTS REPORT BACK TO VARIOUS AWARDING COMMITTEES THE ACTUAL SPENDING, SENDING DOCUMENTATION WITH RECEIPTS, AND WRITE PROGRESS TOWARDS GOALS AND OBJECTIVES THAT WERE SET UPON AWARD OF THE FUNDS. THESE REPORTS ARE REVIEWED BY THE APPROPRIATE COMMITTEE FOR THE SATISFACTORY PROGRESS TOWARD GOALS AND OBJECTIVES.
